channel.description:
[b]This is easy stuff.[/b] But I searched and there is NO tutorials on the renamed way of doing it.

So basically, in your Client Class, Search for one object from this string:
[code]
	        aRSImageProducer_1110.initDrawingArea();
		sprite.method346(382, 0);
		aRSImageProducer_1111.initDrawingArea();
		sprite.method346(-255, 0);

[/code]

They should be two when you find it. The first is responsible for drawing the left side. The second one is the part that Flips and Draws the Right Side. So in order to sop that from happening, we have to block/remove it.  You can remove it, but I prefer commenting it out. So Comment out ALL of this like shown using /* and */

[code]
		/*aRSImageProducer_1110.initDrawingArea();
		sprite.method346(382, 0);
		aRSImageProducer_1111.initDrawingArea();
		sprite.method346(-255, 0);
		aRSImageProducer_1107.initDrawingArea();
		sprite.method346(254, 0);
		aRSImageProducer_1108.initDrawingArea();
		sprite.method346(180, -371);
		aRSImageProducer_1109.initDrawingArea();
		sprite.method346(180, -171);
		aRSImageProducer_1112.initDrawingArea();
		sprite.method346(382, -265);
		aRSImageProducer_1113.initDrawingArea();
		sprite.method346(-180, -265);
		aRSImageProducer_1114.initDrawingArea();
		sprite.method346(254, -171);
		aRSImageProducer_1115.initDrawingArea();*/
[/code]

Now whether you choose to load from your Cache, or by placing in image in your cacher directory, it shouldn't flip. Seamless, easy, beauty for your client. Have fun.
